foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: *The Department of State's FOIA Annual Report for FY 2015 reported that the number of cases pending at the end of the fiscal year for State was 21,750. As a result of our data reconciliation and validation efforts, we have determined that the number of pending requests at the start of FY 2016 in our primary case management system was 11,722. The overall number of cases pending action at that time was closer to the 21,750 number previously reported.

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: *The Department of State's FOIA Annual Report for FY 2015 reported that the number of appeals pending at the end of the fiscal year for State was 393. As a result of our data reconciliation and validation efforts, we have determined that the number should have been 394; that corrected number is reflected here.

foia:PendingPerfectedRequestsSection.foia:FootnoteText: We have included 16,190 referrals from DHS/USCIS in this chart; however, all of the cases have not been entered into the Department's case management system. Therefore, the median and average numbers of days do not reflect those cases.

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: The number of backlogged requests includes an estimated 16,190 referrals received from DHS/USCIS that were not entered into the Department's case management system [see Section V.A]. The estimate is included in the number of requests backlogged as of the end of the fiscal year.

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: * In FY 2015, the Department's case management system tracked FOIA requests filed directly with the Department, those that were received from another agency for consultation, and those that were referred from another agency for processing and direct response by the Department to the requester. The tracking system was modified for FY 2016 and this chart only lists consultations.

**As reported in the Department of State's FOIA Annual Report FY 2015, the number of consultations pending at the end of the fiscal year was 3,256. As a result of our data reconciliation and validation efforts, we have determined that the number reported here โ 280 โ is correct.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: * The Department of State's FOIA Annual Report for FY 2015 reported that the number of cases pending at the end of the fiscal year for State was 21,750. As a result of our data reconciliation and validation efforts, we have determined that the number should have been 11,722; that corrected number is reflected here.
